main_text: I got to catsit these two rescue brothers for my downstairs neighbors for over a week! Started off a bit rough they hadn't been left alone overnight since being adopted. When I first came over Cocoa (black and white) wouldn't come out from under the sofa while I was there so I had to put food in the room and shut the door so his brother Pepper wouldn't eat it. After a couple of days we were all buddies! I'd stop by to hang out and read or watch a warriors game or sit at the window and watch birds with the little guys (they go a bit nuts when crows land on the sidewalk). They're young and still a bit crazy when night fell they would literally climb the walls and sprint the length of the flat. Melanie is allergic so I would change clothes on the back stairs before each visit - don't think any neighbors saw me in my underwear out back. I already miss the fluff brothers and can't wait until the neighbors go away again. Don't tell them but I'd pay to watch their cats!#cocoa #pepper #fluffbrothers #catsit #rescuecats #crazycats #prettyboys
